{"key":"processedPost-10851364","value":{"id":10851364,"first":10850962,"last":10875477,"when":1250173048,"utime":"08/13/09 05:17 PM","content":"Let us know how the vikur works out.&nbsp; The main benefit of vermiculite is it holds a lot of water, like a mineral sponge.&nbsp; Test the vikur to see if it holds water and if you can take a handful and squeeze the water out.&nbsp; If not, it's probably a better substitute for perlite in your terrarium.&nbsp; You can make brf cakes with coir instead of vermiculite, but they don't perform quite as well.<br />RR","title":"Re: no perlite or vermiculite :(","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}